<br>
 Spell Shield is a spell we now have, that we can buff another class with, it allows one to absorb 700 hp of magical damage. Some of the fights now pretty much require it's use to be chain casted, in order to keep the MT up.<br>
<br>
Many of the FT items are no drop, some like the boots of flowing slime are not, but I think of all my FT items, the boots are the only thing that are droppable. Soulstice earring is can be gottent though, yet a person wouldn't go to that effort just for FT1.<br>
<br>
 As far as mana regen is concerned, don't forget the mana conservation items, much like the old saying, a penny saved is a penny earned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=retrievil>Retrievil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/6/03 3:26:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25246.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://whitepapers.homestead.com/files/reticon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What makes your wizard fun to play?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>do it harder, and faster than anyone else, and have the best lasting power of any caster<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
